OL,6,FAlison Fleming, who also produced the
OL,7,Fprogramme, hears the personal
OL,8,Ftestimonies of three devastated
OL,9,Ffamilies who lost loved ones during
OL,10,Fthe pandemic.
OL,12,FHer report features a the son of a fit
OL,13,Fand healthy 90-year-old woman who died
OL,14,Fin hospital during the second wave,
OL,15,Fthe mother of a 23-year-old man who
OL,16,Fdied in her arms waiting for an
OL,17,Fambulance and the wife of a man with
OL,18,Fearly onset dementia who had to die
OL,19,Falone, confused and distressed that
OL,20,Fhis family weren't allowed to be with
OL,21,Fhim.
